Package: nmainla
Type: Package
Title: Network Meta-Analysis using Integrated Nested Laplace Approximations
Version: 0.1.0
Date: 2016-12-10
Authors@R: c(
   person("Burak Kursad", "Gunhan", email = "burak.gunhan@med.uni-goettingen.de", role = c("aut", "cre")),
   person("Rafael", "Sauter", email = "rafael.sauter@uzh.ch", role = c("aut")))
Description: An R package for performing network meta-analysis using integrated nested Laplace approximations ('INLA'). It includes methods to assess the heterogeneity and inconsistency in the network. The installation of R package 'INLA' is compulsory for successful usage. The 'INLA' package can be obtained from <http://www.r-inla.org>. We recommend the testing version, which can be downloaded by running: source("http://www.math.ntnu.no/inla/givemeINLA-testing.R").
License: GPL (>= 2)
LazyData: TRUE
Depends: R (>= 2.10)
Additional_repositories: http://www.math.ntnu.no/inla/R/testing
RoxygenNote: 5.0.1
Suggests: INLA,
    knitr,
    testthat
VignetteBuilder: knitr
URL: http://github.com/gunhanb/nmainla
BugReports: http://github.com/gunhanb/nmainla/issues


